Token.Abstract: The WSCKeychainManager class enables you to perform many generic keychain operations and insulates an app from the underlying Keychain Services.
The WSCKeychainManager object's delegate.
The WSCKeychainManager object's delegate.
The WSCKeychainManager object's delegate.

Returns the shared keychain manager object for the process.
This method always returns the same keychain manager object. If you plan to use a delegate with keychain manager to receive notifications about the completion of keychain operations, you should create a new instance of WSCKeychainManager (using the init method ) rather than using the shared object.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The default WSCKeychainManager object for the keychain services.

Token.Abstract: Creates and returns a WSCKeychain object using the given URL, passphrase, and inital permitted operations.

Parameter.Name: _URL
Parameter.Abstract: Specify the URL in which the new keychain should be sotred. The URL in this parameter must not be a file reference URL or an URL other than file scheme This parameter must not be nil.

Parameter.Name: _PermittedOperations
Parameter.Abstract: An array of WSCPermittedOperation object indicating the initial permitted operations for the new keychain, A keychain's permitted operations determine which application have permission to user the keychain. You may pass nil for the standard permitted operations.

Parameter.Name: _Passphrase
Parameter.Abstract: A NSString object containing the passphrase which is used to protect the new keychain. This parameter must not be nil.

Parameter.Name: _WillBecomeDefault
Parameter.Abstract: A BOOL value representing whether to set the new keychain as default keychain.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information. You may specify nil for this parameter if you don't want the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: A WSCKeychain object initialized with above parameters.

Token.Abstract: Creates and returns a WSCKeychain object using the given URL, interaction prompt and inital permitted operations.

Parameter.Name: _URL
Parameter.Abstract: Specify the URL in which the new keychain should be sotred. The URL in this parameter must not be a file reference URL or an URL other than file scheme This parameter must not be nil.

Parameter.Name: _PermittedOperations
Parameter.Abstract: An array of WSCPermittedOperation object indicating the initial permitted operations for the new keychain, A keychain's permitted operations determine which application have permission to user the keychain. You may pass nil for the standard permitted operations.

Parameter.Name: _WillBecomeDefault
Parameter.Abstract: A BOOL value representing whether to set the new keychain as default keychain.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information. You may specify nil for this parameter if you don't want the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: A WSCKeychain object initialized with above parameters as well as a passphrase, which is obtained from the passphrase dialog.

Token.Abstract: Opens an existing keychain from the location specified by a given URL.

Parameter.Name: _URLOfExistingKeychain
Parameter.Abstract: The file URL that identifies the keychain file you want to open. The URL in this parameter must be a file reference URL. This parameter must not be nil.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information. You may specify nil for this parameter if you don't want the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: A WSCKeychain object represented an existing keychain located at the given URL.

Token.Abstract: Deletes the specified keychains from the default keychain search list, and removes the keychain itself if it is a keychain file stored locally.

Parameter.Name: _Keychain
Parameter.Abstract: A single keychain object you wish to delete. To delete more than one keychain, please use deleteKeychains:error: method. Passing nil to this parameter returns an NSError object which encapsulated WSCCommonInvalidParametersError error code.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information. You may specify nil for this parameter if you don't want the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the keychain was deleted successfully or if _Keychain was nil. Returns NO if an error occured. If the delegate aborts the operation for a keychain, this method returns YES.

Token.Abstract: Deletes one or more keychains specified in an array from the default keychain search list, and removes the keychain itself if it is a file stored locally.

Parameter.Name: _Keychains
Parameter.Abstract: An array of keychains you wish to delete. To delete keychain one by one, please use deleteKeychain:error: method. This parameter must NOT be nil, passing nil to this parameter just returns an NSError object which encapsulated WSCCommonInvalidParametersError error code directly instead of calling any delegate method in WSCKeychainManagerDelegate delegate protocol.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information. You may specify nil for this parameter if you don't want the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the keychain was deleted successfully or if _Keychain was nil. Returns NO if an error occured. If the delegate aborts the operation for a keychain, this method returns YES.

Token.Abstract:
Sets the specified keychain as default keychain.
In most cases, your application should not need to set the default keychain, because this is a choice normally made by the user. You may call this method to change where a passphrase or other keychain items are added, but since this is a user choice, you should set the default keychain back to the user specified keychain when you are done.

Parameter.Name: _Keychain
Parameter.Abstract: The keychain you wish to make the default.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information. You may specify nil for this parameter if you don't want the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The older default keychain if the specified keychain was made default successfully. If there is not an older default keychain (perhaps the older default keychain has been deleted, moved or renamed), returns nil. Returns nil if an error occured. If the delegate aborts the operation for the keychain, this method returns nil.

Token.Abstract: Retrieves a WSCKeychain object represented the current default keychain.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: A WSCKeychain object represented the current default keychain.

Token.Abstract: Lock the specified keychain.

Parameter.Name: _Keychain
Parameter.Abstract: The keychain you wish to lock. Passing nil to this parameter returns an NSError object which encapsulated WSCCommonInvalidParametersError error code. And passing an invalid keychain to this parameter returns an NSError object which encapsulated WSCKeychainIsInvalidError error code.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the specified keychain was locked successfully; otherwise, NO.

Token.Abstract: Locks all keychains lying in the current default search list belonging to the current user.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if all the keychains were locked successfully; otherwise, NO.

Token.Abstract: Unlocks a keychain with an explicitly provided passphrase.

Parameter.Name: _Keychain
Parameter.Abstract: The keychain you wish to unlock. Passing nil to this parameter returns an NSError object which encapsulated WSCCommonInvalidParametersError error code. And passing an invalid keychain to this parameter returns an NSError object which encapsulated WSCKeychainIsInvalidError error code.

Parameter.Name: _Passphrase
Parameter.Abstract: A string containing the passphrase for the specified keychain. This parameter must NOT be nil.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the specified keychain was unlocked successfully; otherwise, NO.

Token.Abstract: Unlocks a keychain with the user interaction which is used to retrieve passphrase from the user.

Parameter.Name: _Keychain
Parameter.Abstract: The keychain you wish to unlock. Passing nil to this parameter returns an NSError object which encapsulated WSCCommonInvalidParametersError error code. And passing an invalid keychain to this parameter returns an NSError object which encapsulated WSCKeychainIsInvalidError error code.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the specified keychain was unlocked successfully; otherwise, NO.

Token.Abstract: Retrieves a keychain search list.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The keychain search list for current user. Returns nil if an error occurs. Returns an empty array if the current keychain search list is empty.

Token.Abstract: Specifies the list of keychains to use in the default keychain search list.

Parameter.Name: _SearchList
Parameter.Abstract: An array of keychain objects (of class WSCKeychain specifying the list of keychains to use in the new default keychain search list. Passing an empty array clears the search list. This parameter must NOT be nil.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: On input, a pointer to an error object. If an error occurs, this pointer is set to an actual error object containing the error information.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The older default keychain search list if the current keychain search list was updated successfully. Returns nil if an error occured. If the delegate aborts the operation for the keychain, this method returns nil.

Token.Abstract: Addes the specified keychain to the current default search list.

And passing an invalid keychain to this parameter returns an NSError object which encapsulated WSCKeychainIsInvalidError error code.
